messages.messageBody:
>>We discussed that Ted Neely is an actor, that they
wouldn't actually injure their actor, that Judas wasn't really hanged
(seeing him
step back on the bus was reassuring <g>), and that being aware of what you
can
personally handle is important.<<
If he liked Ted Neely he can listen to him in a recent show called
"Rasputin" where he plays the title role. (I saw it at the Grand opera
house in Wilmington DE) An excellent show (and I'd say that even if my
brother Shane Gosdis weren't in it!) :) Seriously, though the music is
great and the story touches on an extremely interesting time in Russian
History. There's no video yet but There's a CD and a web site.
http://rasputinthemusical.com/

Cheers,
Krisula
